    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Subtractive process which progressively removes base metals from a gold-containing alloy to produce a nearly pure layer of gold. Depletion gilding was used in ancient Greece, in Egypt in the second century BC, and in pre-Columbian America.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
